<inglise> (a) direct discrimination shall be taken to occur where one person is treated less favourably than another is, has been or would be treated in a comparable situation on grounds of racial or ethnic origin; </inglise>
<eesti> a) otseseks diskrimineerimiseks peetakse seda, kui &uuml;hte inimest koheldakse rassilise v&otilde;i etnilise p&auml;ritolu t&otilde;ttu halvemini, kui on koheldud, koheldakse v&otilde;i v&otilde;idakse kohelda teist isikut samalaadses olukorras; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) indirect discrimination shall be taken to occur where an apparently neutral provision, criterion or practice would put persons of a racial or ethnic origin at a particular disadvantage compared with other persons, unless that provision, criterion or practice is objectively justified by a legitimate aim and the means of achieving that aim are appropriate and necessary. </inglise>
<eesti> b) kaudseks diskrimineerimiseks peetakse seda, kui ilmselt neutraalne s&auml;te, kriteerium v&otilde;i tava seab isikud rassilise v&otilde;i etnilise p&auml;ritolu alusel teistega v&otilde;rreldes ebasoodsamasse olukorda, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui k&otilde;nealune s&auml;te, kriteerium v&otilde;i tava on objektiivselt p&otilde;hjendatud &otilde;igustatud eesm&auml;rgiga ja selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamise vahendid on asjakohased ja vajalikud. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Harassment shall be deemed to be discrimination within the meaning of paragraph 1, when an unwanted conduct related to racial or ethnic origin takes place with the purpose or effect of violating the dignity of a person and of creating an intimidating, hostile, degrading, humiliating or offensive environment. </inglise>
<eesti> Ahistamist peetakse diskrimineerimiseks l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses, kui rassilise v&otilde;i etnilise p&auml;ritoluga seotud soovimatu k&auml;itumise eem&auml;rk v&otilde;i selle tegelik toime on isiku v&auml;&auml;rikuse alandamine ja &auml;hvardava, vaenuliku, alandava v&otilde;i solvava &otilde;hkkonna loomine. </eesti>
<inglise> In this context, the concept of harassment may be defined in accordance with the national laws and practice of the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Selles kontekstis v&otilde;ib ahistamise m&otilde;iste m&auml;&auml;ratleda vastavalt liikmesriikide siseriiklikule &otilde;igusele ja tavale. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> An instruction to discriminate against persons on grounds of racial or ethnic origin shall be deemed to be discrimination within the meaning of paragraph 1. </inglise>
